[slide]
# HTML
## body

The `BODY` tag is a normal element that contains page content. This area contains mostly visible content.

||code html||
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head> ... </head>
	<body>
		...
	</body>
</html>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## h1

The `H1` tag is a normal, block element that can contain content.

||code html||
<body>
	<h1>Hello, World!</h1>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<h1>Hello, World</h1>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## Block Elements

A `block` element will stack on top of each other. This can be redefined with CSS, but by default, `H1` is a block element.

||code html||
<body>
	<h1>Top</h1>
	<h1>Bottom</h1>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<h1>Top</h1>
<h1>Bottom</h1>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## span

The `SPAN` tag is a normal, inline element that can contain content.

||code html||
<body>
	<span>Hello, World!</span>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<span>Hello, World</span>
</div>




[slide]
# HTML
## Inline Elements

An `inline` element will stack next to each other. This can be redefined with CSS, but by default, `SPAN` is an inline element.

||code html||
<body>
	<span>First</span>
	<span>Second</span>
	<span>Third</span>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<span>First</span>
<span>Second</span>
<span>Third</span>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## div

The `DIV` is a normal, block element that can contain content.

||code html||
<body>
	<div>content</div>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<div>content</div>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## ul

The `UL` is a normal, block element that can contain `LI` elements. It is use to create unordered lists _(bullets)_

||code html||
<body>
	<ul>
		<li>First</li>
		<li>Second</li>
		<li>Third</li>
	</ul>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<ul>
	<li>First</li>
	<li>Second</li>
	<li>Third</li>
</ul>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## ol

The `OL` is a normal, block element that can contain `LI` elements. It is use to create ordered lists _(numbered)_

||code html||
<body>
	<ol>
		<li>First</li>
		<li>Second</li>
		<li>Third</li>
	</ol>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<ol>
	<li>First</li>
	<li>Second</li>
	<li>Third</li>
</ol>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## table

The `TABLE` is a normal, inline element that is used to display tabular data.

||code html||
<table>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>1</td> <td>First</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>2</td> <td>Second</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<table>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>1</td>
			<td>First</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>2</td>
			<td>Second</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>
</div>




[slide]
# HTML
## a

The `A` tag _(Anchor)_ is a normal, inline element that is used to navigate to new urls or act as a target.

||code html||
<body>
	<a href="http://google.com" >
		Google.com
	</a>
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<a href="http://google.com" >
	Google.com
</a>
</div>



[slide]
# HTML
## img

The `IMG` is a void, inline element that is used to display images.

||code html||
<body>
	<img src="./html-logo.png" />
	<img src="http://lorempixel.com/100/100/food" />
</body>
||code||

<div class="output" >
<img src="./html-logo.png" />
<img src="http://lorempixel.com/100/100/food" />
</div>